Write a Java program to find the closest pair of points from a given array of coordinates

### Response:
public static double[] closestPair(int[][] points) {
    int closest_distance = Integer.MAX_VALUE;
    int[] closest_pair = new int[2]; 

    for (int i = 0; i < points.length - 1; i++) {
        for (int j = i+1; j < points.length; j++) {
            int xDist = Math.abs(points[i][0] - points[j][0]);
            int yDist = Math.abs(points[i][1] - points[j][1]);
            int distance = xDist + yDist;
            if (distance < closest_distance) {
                closest_distance = distance;
                closest_pair[0] = i;
                closest_pair[1] = j;
            }
        }
    }
    return closest_pair;
}

int[][] points = {{2, 3}, {12, 30}, {40, 50}, {5, 1}, {12, 10}}; 
